channel.title: GodzHell - Voting without users knowledge
channel.description:
I recently discovered that their webclient will download a jar file that will vote on various sites for various servers without the user even knowing it. If you have ever used their webclient, listen in.
To find out if you have this (you most likely will), go to start and search for 'msconfig' and open it, then go to the 'Startup' tab and search if you have it, it will look exactly like this:
[IMG]http://i40.tinypic.com/6ej1bs.png[/img]
If you navigate to that folder, you can see that there is a .jar. When extracted, these files will appear:
[img]http://i42.tinypic.com/34phyk2.png[/img]
If you decompile these files, you can see that they are requesting information to vote on various sites, without you even knowing.
A bit of RS1.class:
[img]http://i44.tinypic.com/23gy7g1.png[/img]
And when you visit one of these URL's:
[img]http://i42.tinypic.com/24ez21e.png[/img]
It will start up when you boot your computer. My advice would be to delete the folder and do a virus scan. I'm not sure if this happens with the other servers they are affiliated with, so check for that aswell.
